library(ggplot2)

#     
numeric_columns <- c("Rental_Value", "Floor", "Total_Floors", "Area")

options(repr.plot.width=20, repr.plot.height=10)  #    

for (col in numeric_columns) {
  bin_width <- ifelse(col == "Rental_Value", 400, ifelse(col == "Area", 5, 1))  #   ( )

  p <- ggplot(flats, aes_string(x = col)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = bin_width, fill = "blue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
    ggtitle(paste(":", col)) +
    theme_minimal()

  print(p)
}

#   (boxplot)   
for (col in numeric_columns) {
  p <- ggplot(flats, aes_string(x = "' '", y = col)) +
    geom_boxplot(fill = "red", alpha = 0.5) +
    ggtitle(paste(" :", col)) +
    theme_minimal()
  print(p)  #    
}

pairs(flats[, numeric_columns], main = " ")

# ,   
model <- lm(Rental_Value ~ Area, data = flats)

#     
new_data <- data.frame(Area = seq(min(flats$Area), max(flats$Area), length.out = 100))

#      
predictions <- predict(model, newdata = new_data, interval = "prediction")

#     
new_data$fit <- predictions[, "fit"]
new_data$lwr_pred <- predictions[, "lwr"]
new_data$upr_pred <- predictions[, "upr"]

#  
ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = flats, aes(x = Area, y = Rental_Value), color = "blue", alpha = 0.6) +  #  
  geom_smooth(data = flats, aes(x = Area, y = Rental_Value), method = "lm", color = "red", fill = "red", level = 0.95) +  #  
  geom_ribbon(data = new_data, aes(x = Area, ymin = lwr_pred, ymax = upr_pred), fill = "gray", alpha = 0.3) +  #  
  geom_line(data = new_data, aes(x = Area, y = fit), color = "black", linewidth = 1) +  #  
  ggtitle("       ") +
  theme_minimal()
